eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities

Class SimpleBidirectionalMap<L,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.SimpleBidirectionalMap<L,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    L -
    R -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BidirectionalMap<L,R>, java.io.Serializable

    public class SimpleBidirectionalMap<L,R>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BidirectionalMap<L,R>
    [DELETEME_LATER: imported from BIUTEE 2.4.1. infrastructure without modification] An implementation of BidirectionalMap that uses two java.util.Maps as underlying maps, and keeps them compatible with each other to represent exactly one-to-one mapping.

    Not thread safe!
    null values behavior is undefined (never tested).

    Author:
    Asher Stern
